history.content: In my experience, you need to have taken and passed all classes you need to graduate in order to take any techs P/NP (so it's not possible).

I would like to PNP one of my technicals, since I'm currently enrolled in 18 units with 16 being techs plus a handful of extracurriculars. However I am one class short of the 20 EECS upper division units. So I have no way to not meeting that requirement with my other classes this semester (short of me dropping or failing all 3 other classes). I know the rule is that you need to fulfill all your major requirements before you can PNP, but does this include classes concurrently enrolled in?
history.subject: PNP Tech with Concurrent Enrollment that Fulfills Requirement
